  "title": "Electrical Engineer (Low/Medium Voltage, Built Environment)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Supervise testing and commissioning of electrical equipment on-site and manage the review and submission of site acceptance test reports.</li>\n  <li>Review and interpret Single Line Diagrams and Electrical Schematic Drawings.</li>\n  <li>Support electrical equipment installation inspections to ensure compliance with standards.</li>\n  <li>Participate in site activities and meetings with clients and contractors.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Electrical Engineering.</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years’ local experience in <strong>LV/MV electrical equipment installation, testing, commissioning, or maintenance </strong>within the <strong>built environment sector.</strong></li>\n  <li>Possess initiative and able to work in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
